<p><h2 align=center>Useful links about software</h2>

<p>SAS and SPSS are available in all the <a
href="http://labs.circa.ufl.edu/cse.html">CIRCA labs</a>, such as CSE
211.

<p><h3>SPSS:</h3> A student version of SPSS is available at the UF
Bookstore next to Reitz Union.  
You can get it more cheaply for your home PC
with a one-year license through the <a
href="http://www.software.ufl.edu/spss/">Student Home-Use Program</a>.
You may prefer to use the full-fledged version of SPSS in CIRCA labs.

<p>When getting started, it can be helpful to use a primer such as
"SPSS for Windows Step by Step" by D. George and P. Mallery.

<p>Here are some basic instructions for <a
href="appendix.pdf">using SPSS and
SAS</a> for various statistical analyses (pdf file).  The first half
deals with SPSS.  This is a revised version of the appendix in the
course text, and is being updated for the fourth edition.  Please
point out any errors you notice.


